25/11/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Local media reported Wednesday (November 24th) that the flow of illegal immigrants trying to enter the EU through Greece has dropped significantly since the deployment of EU border police. 
According to private radio SKAI, 2,150 illegal migrants have been arrested by Frontex team members and Greek border police since the beginning of November. 
The Frontex border guards began working in the area between the villages of Nea Vyssa and Orestiada in the northeast part of the country on November 5th. 
(SKAI, DPA - 24/11/10)
